<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.ico">
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>BusinessSpew — API Reference</title>
  <style>
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    body {
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2c3e50 0%, #3498db 100%);
      min-height: 100vh;
      color: #ecf0f1;
      padding: 0 0 60px;
    }

    header {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 40px 20px 30px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
      margin-bottom: 40px;
    }

    header h1 { font-size: 2em; }
    header p  { margin-top: 8px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); font-size: 0.95em; }
    header a  { color: #00ffcc; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.9em; }
    header a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    .container {
      max-width: 860px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 20px;
    }

    /* ── Base URL badge ───────────────────────────── */
    .base-url {
      background: rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
      border-left: 4px solid #00ffcc;
      padding: 14px 20px;
      border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
      font-family: monospace;
      font-size: 1em;
      margin-bottom: 40px;
      color: #00ffcc;
    }
    .base-url span { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); font-size: 0.85em; font-family: sans-serif; display: block; margin-bottom: 4px; }

    /* ── Endpoint cards ───────────────────────────── */
    .endpoint {
      background: rgba(44, 62, 80, 0.85);
      border-radius: 8px;
      margin-bottom: 28px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .endpoint-header {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 14px;
      padding: 16px 20px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    }

    .method {
      font-family: monospace;
      font-weight: bold;
      font-size: 0.8em;
      padding: 4px 10px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      min-width: 52px;
      text-align: center;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    }
    .method.get  { background: #27ae60; color: #fff; }
    .method.post { background: #e67e22; color: #fff; }

    .path {
      font-family: monospace;
      font-size: 1em;
      color: #00ffcc;
      flex: 1;
    }

    .summary {
      font-size: 0.88em;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);
    }

    .endpoint-body {
      padding: 18px 20px;
    }

    .endpoint-body p {
      font-size: 0.93em;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8);
      line-height: 1.6;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }

    /* ── Params table ─────────────────────────────── */
    table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      font-size: 0.88em;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    th {
      text-align: left;
      padding: 8px 12px;
      background: rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      font-size: 0.8em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }
    td {
      padding: 9px 12px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
      vertical-align: top;
    }
    td:first-child { font-family: monospace; color: #00ffcc; white-space: nowrap; }
    td.optional    { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4); font-size: 0.85em; }
    tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }

    /* ── Example blocks ───────────────────────────── */
    .label {
      font-size: 0.75em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4);
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }

    pre {
      background: rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
      padding: 14px 16px;
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-family: monospace;
      font-size: 0.85em;
      color: #00ffcc;
      overflow-x: auto;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
      white-space: pre;
    }

    /* ── Section headings ─────────────────────────── */
    h2 {
      font-size: 1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4);
      margin: 36px 0 16px;
      padding-bottom: 6px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    }

    /* ── Auth callout ─────────────────────────────── */
    .auth-note {
      background: rgba(52, 152, 219, 0.12);
      border-left: 4px solid #3498db;
      padding: 14px 20px;
      border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
      font-size: 0.9em;
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 40px;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8);
    }
    .auth-note code {
      font-family: monospace;
      color: #00ffcc;
      background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
      padding: 2px 6px;
      border-radius: 3px;
    }
    .auth-note a { color: #00ffcc; text-decoration: none; }
    .auth-note a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    footer {
      text-align: center;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.3);
      font-size: 0.85em;
      margin-top: 60px;
    }
    footer a { color: #3498db; text-decoration: none; }
    footer a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    .footer-key-note { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 0.82em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.2); }
    .footer-key-note a { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35); }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <h1>BusinessSpew 🔥 — API Reference</h1>
  <p>All endpoints return JSON. Generation endpoints require an <code style="font-family:monospace;color:#00ffcc;">X-API-Key</code> header.</p>
  <p style="margin-top:12px"><a href="/">← Back to home</a></p>
</header>

<div class="container">

  <div class="base-url">
    <span>Base URL</span>
    https://api.leveragedsynergies.com
  </div>

  <div class="auth-note">
    <strong>Authentication</strong> &mdash; pass your API key as an HTTP header on every generation request:<br>
    <code>X-API-Key: your-key-here</code><br><br>
    <code>GET /api</code> and <code>GET /health</code> are public.
    To request a key, <a href="#" data-n="webmagic" data-d="websembly" data-t="com"
      onclick="window.location='mailto:'+this.dataset.n+'@'+this.dataset.d+'.'+this.dataset.t;return false;">contact us</a>.
  </div>

  <!-- ── STATUS ──────────────────────────────────── -->
  <h2>Status &amp; Discovery</h2>

  <div class="endpoint">
    <div class="endpoint-header">
      <span class="method get">GET</span>
      <span class="path">/api</span>
      <span class="summary">Service status and available topics</span>
    </div>
    <div class="endpoint-body">
      <p>Returns the service name, version, operational status, loaded vocabulary topics, and available route list. Useful for checking whether the vocabulary loaded successfully from S3.</p>
      <div class="label">Example response</div>
      <pre>{
  "name": "Business Spew",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "status": "running",
  "categories": ["tech"],
  "services": ["/spew", "/api"]
}</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="endpoint">
    <div class="endpoint-header">
      <span class="method get">GET</span>
      <span class="path">/health</span>
      <span class="summary">Liveness check</span>
    </div>
    <div class="endpoint-body">
      <p>Lightweight health check for load balancers and uptime monitors. Returns <code>200 ok</code> when vocabulary is loaded, <code>503 degraded</code> if S3 vocabulary is unavailable.</p>
      <div class="label">Example response (healthy)</div>
      <pre>{ "status": "ok" }</pre>
      <div class="label">Example response (degraded)</div>
      <pre>{ "status": "degraded", "reason": "vocabulary not loaded" }</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── GENERATION ──────────────────────────────── -->
  <h2>Generation</h2>

  <div class="endpoint">
    <div class="endpoint-header">
      <span class="method get">GET</span>
      <span class="path">/api/:topic/:sentences?/:paragraphs?/:title?</span>
      <span class="summary">Generate spew for a specific topic</span>
    </div>
    <div class="endpoint-body">
      <p>Generates corporate jargon sentences scoped to the named vocabulary topic. All parameters after <code>:topic</code> are optional and positional.</p>
      <table>
        <tr><th>Segment</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
        <tr><td>:topic</td><td>String</td><td>—</td><td>Vocabulary category (e.g. <code>tech</code>). Returns 404 with available topics if not found.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>:sentences</td><td>Integer</td><td class="optional">3</td><td>Sentences per paragraph.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>:paragraphs</td><td>Integer</td><td class="optional">1</td><td>Number of paragraphs to generate.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>:title</td><td>String</td><td class="optional">generated</td><td>Document title. Auto-generated from topic vocabulary if omitted.</td></tr>
      </table>
      <div class="label">Examples</div>
      <pre>GET /api/tech
X-API-Key: your-key-here</pre>
      <pre>GET /api/tech/2/4/My%20Title
X-API-Key: your-key-here</pre>
      <div class="label">Example response</div>
      <pre>{
  "title": "Stakeholder Maps Initiative",
  "topic": "tech",
  "paragraphs": [
    "We will endeavor to leverage synergy playbooks. ..."
  ]
}</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="endpoint">
    <div class="endpoint-header">
      <span class="method get">GET</span>
      <span class="path">/api/:sentences?/:paragraphs?/:title?</span>
      <span class="summary">Generate spew from a random topic</span>
    </div>
    <div class="endpoint-body">
      <p>Identical to the topic route above but selects a vocabulary topic at random. All segments are optional.</p>
      <div class="label">Examples</div>
      <pre>GET /api/3/2
X-API-Key: your-key-here</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="endpoint">
    <div class="endpoint-header">
      <span class="method post">POST</span>
      <span class="path">/spew</span>
      <span class="summary">Generate spew via JSON body</span>
    </div>
    <div class="endpoint-body">
      <p>Accepts a JSON body. All fields are optional — omit any to use the default.</p>
      <table>
        <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
        <tr><td>sentences</td><td>Integer</td><td class="optional">3</td><td>Sentences per paragraph.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>paragraphs</td><td>Integer</td><td class="optional">1</td><td>Number of paragraphs.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>category</td><td>String</td><td class="optional">random</td><td>Vocabulary topic. Falls back to random if omitted or unrecognised.</td></tr>
      </table>
      <div class="label">Example request</div>
      <pre>POST /spew
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: your-key-here

{ "sentences": 2, "paragraphs": 3, "category": "tech" }</pre>
      <div class="label">Example response</div>
      <pre>{
  "paragraphs": [
    "We must seize the moment and optimize ROIs. ...",
    "Take the customer's temperature and then you can ...",
    "Success is not a crap-shoot if we leverage ..."
  ]
}</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── ADMIN ───────────────────────────────────── -->
  <h2>Admin</h2>

  <div class="endpoint">
    <div class="endpoint-header">
      <span class="method post">POST</span>
      <span class="path">/admin/reload</span>
      <span class="summary">Reload vocabulary from S3</span>
    </div>
    <div class="endpoint-body">
      <p>Forces a re-fetch of all vocabulary JSON files from S3 without restarting the process. Returns the refreshed category list on success. ⚠️ Authentication not yet enforced — do not expose publicly.</p>
      <div class="label">Example response (success)</div>
      <pre>{ "status": "ok", "categories": ["tech"] }</pre>
      <div class="label">Example response (S3 unreachable)</div>
      <pre>{ "status": "error", "reason": "S3 Error: ..." }</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

</div><!-- /.container -->

<footer>
  BusinessSpew <%= app_version %> | Built with ❤️ in memory of Wilson A. Rogers |
  <a href="https://fly.io">Deployed on Fly.io</a>
  <p class="footer-key-note">
    API key required for generation endpoints &mdash;
    <a href="#" data-n="webmagic" data-d="websembly" data-t="com"
       onclick="window.location='mailto:'+this.dataset.n+'@'+this.dataset.d+'.'+this.dataset.t;return false;">request one here</a>.
  </p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
